<DOC><DOCNO> AP901024-0244 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NY-10-24-90 1331EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f PM-Dollar-Gold 1stLd-Writethru f0014 10-24 0252</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Dollar-Gold, 1st Ld-Writethru, f0014,0289</SECOND><HEAD>Dollar Drops, Gold Largely Unchanged</HEAD><NOTE>Eds: New thruout with closing prices in Europe, midday quotes inNew York.</NOTE><DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The U.S. dollar dropped today against most majorcurrencies in directionless trading in Europe. Gold was littlechangedfirst of four specials in a 1990-91 ``Vision andValues'' series presented by the Interfaith BroadcastingCommission.   In ``The Common Good,'' differing perspectives on right choicesare brought out about community issues in economically depressedBarbour County, W.Va., and in affluent Westchester County, N.Y.   Sociologist Robert Bellah of the University of California saysthat as a principle, the ``common good'' is urgent these days ``aswe are seeing that if individuals simply seek to maximize their ownwelfare, they produce not a common good, but a common bad.''   The interfaith commission also includes the U.S. CatholicConference, the Jewish Theological Seminary of America and theSouthern Baptist Radio and Film Commission.   The second special in the series, ``Winds of Freedom,'' aboutchanges in Eastern Europe, is scheduled to air Dec. 2.</TEXT><NOTE>End Adv for Fri AMs, Oct. 26</NOTE><TEXT/></DOC>